291 static void abc_extractkeyvalue(char *key, size_t key_max,
292  char *value, size_t value_max, const char *src)
293 {
294  while (*src && isspace(*src))
295  src++;
296 
297  size_t key_size;
298  for (key_size = 0; key_size < key_max - 1 && *src;) {
299  if (*src == '=') {
300  src++;
301  break;
302  }
303  key[key_size++] = *src++;
304  }
305  while (key_size > 0 && isspace(key[key_size - 1]))
306  key_size--;
307  key[key_size] = '\0';
308 
309  while (*src && isspace(*src))
310  src++;
311 
312  size_t value_size;
313  for (value_size = 0; value_size < value_max - 1 && *src;)
314  value[value_size++] = *src++;
315  while (value_size > 0 && isspace(value[value_size - 1]))
316  value_size--;
317  value[value_size] = '\0';
318 }

342 static uint32_t notelen_notediv_to_ticks(int speed, int len, int div)
343 {
344  uint32_t u;
345  if (div == 0) return 0;
346  u = (ROWSPERNOTE * RESOLUTION * speed * len * global_tempo_factor) / (div * global_tempo_divider);
347  return u;
348 }

350 static void abc_dumptracks(ABCHANDLE *h, const char *p)
351 {
352  ABCTRACK *t;
353  ABCEVENT *e;
354  int n,pat,row,tck;
355  char nn[3];
356  if( !h ) return;
357  for( t=h->track; t; t=t->next ) {
358  printf("track %d.%d chan=%d %s\n", (int)(t->vno), (int)(t->vpos),
359  (int)(t->chan), (char *)(t->v));
360  if( strcmp(p,"nonotes") )
361  n = 1;
362  else
363  n = 0;
364  for( e=t->head; e; e=e->next ) {
365  tck = modticks(e->tracktick);
366  row = tck / h->speed;
367  pat = row / 64;
368  tck = tck % h->speed;
369  row = row % 64;
370  nn[0] = ( e->tracktick % abcticks(h->speed * 64) ) ? ' ': '-';
371  if( e->flg == 1 ) {
372  printf(" %6d.%02d.%d%c%c %d.%d %s ",
373  pat, row, tck, nn[0], (int)(e->part), (int)(t->vno),
374  (int)(t->vpos), (char *)(t->v));
375  if( e->cmd == cmdchord ) {
376  nn[0] = "CCCDDEFFGGAABccddeffggaabb"[e->par[chordnote]];
377  nn[1] = "b # # # # # # # # # # #"[e->par[chordnote]];
378  nn[2] = '\0';
379  if( isspace(nn[1]) ) nn[1] = '\0';
380  printf("CMD %c: gchord %s%s",
381  (char)(e->cmd), nn, chordname[e->par[chordnum]]);
382  if( e->par[chordbase] != e->par[chordnote] ) {
383  nn[0] = "CCCDDEFFGGAABccddeffggaabb"[e->par[chordbase]];
384  nn[1] = "b # # # # # # # # # # #"[e->par[chordbase]];
385  nn[2] = '\0';
386  printf("/%s", nn);
387  }
388  printf("\n");
389  }
390  else
391  printf("CMD %c @%p 0x%08lX\n",
392  (char)(e->cmd), e,
393  (unsigned long)(e->lpar));
394  if( strcmp(p,"nonotes") )
395  n = 1;
396  else
397  n = 0;
398  }
399  else if( n ) {
400  printf(" %6d.%02d.%d%c%c %d.%d %s ", pat, row, tck, nn[0], e->part, t->vno, t->vpos, t->v);
401  if( e->par[note] ) {
402  nn[0] = "CCCDDEFFGGAABccddeffggaabb"[e->par[note]-23];
403  nn[1] = "b # # # # # # # # # # #"[e->par[note]-23];
404  nn[2] = '\0';
405  }
406  else strcpy(nn,"--");
407  printf("NOTE %s octave %d inst %s vol %03d\n",
408  nn, e->par[octave], pat_gm_name(pat_smptogm(e->par[smpno])),e->par[volume]);
409  if( strcmp(p,"all") )
410  n = 0;
411  }
412  }
413  }
414 }

453 static MMFILE *mmfopen(const char *name, const char *mode)
454 {
455  FILE *fp;
456  MMFILE *mmfile;
457  long len;
458  if( *mode != 'r' ) return NULL;
459  fp = fopen(name, mode);
460  if( !fp ) return NULL;
461  fseek(fp, 0, SEEK_END);
462  len = ftell(fp);
463  mmfile = (MMFILE *)malloc(len+sizeof(MMFILE));
464  if( !mmfile ) return NULL;
465  fseek(fp, 0, SEEK_SET);
466  fread(&mmfile[1],1,len,fp);
467  fclose(fp);
468  mmfile->mm = (char *)&mmfile[1];
469  mmfile->sz = len;
470  mmfile->pos = 0;
471  return mmfile;
472 }

486 static int mmfgetc(MMFILE *mmfile)
487 {
488  int b;
489  if( mmfeof(mmfile) ) return EOF;
490  b = mmfile->mm[mmfile->pos];
491  mmfile->pos++;
492  if( b=='\r' && !mmfeof(mmfile) && mmfile->mm[mmfile->pos] == '\n' ) {
493  b = '\n';
494  mmfile->pos++;
495  }
496  return b;
497 }

564 // =============================================================================
565 static void abc_new_macro(ABCHANDLE *h, const char *m)
566 // =============================================================================
567 {
568  ABCMACRO *retval;

570  abc_extractkeyvalue(key, sizeof(key), value, sizeof(value), m);
571

573  retval->name = DupStr(h->macrohandle, key, strlen(key));
574  retval->n = strrchr(retval->name, 'n'); // for transposing macro's

576  retval->next = h->macro;

580 // =============================================================================
581 static void abc_new_umacro(ABCHANDLE *h, const char *m)
582 // =============================================================================
583 {
584  ABCMACRO *retval, *mp;
585  char key[256], value[256];
586  abc_extractkeyvalue(key, sizeof(key), value, sizeof(value), m);
587  if( strlen(key) > 1 || strchr("~HIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXY",toupper(key[0])) == 0 ) return;
588  while( char *q = strchr(key, '!') )
589  *q = '+'; // translate oldstyle to newstyle
590  if( !strcmp(key,"+nil+") ) { // delete a macro
591  mp = NULL;
592  for( retval=h->umacro; retval; retval = retval->next ) {
593  if( retval->name[0] == key[0] ) { // delete this one
594  if( mp ) mp->next = retval->next;
595  else h->umacro = retval->next;
596  _mm_free(h->macrohandle, retval);
597  return;
598  }
599  mp = retval;
600  }
601  return;
602  }
603  retval = (ABCMACRO *)_mm_calloc(h->macrohandle, 1,sizeof(ABCTRACK));
604  retval->name = DupStr(h->macrohandle, key, 1);
605  retval->subst = DupStr(h->macrohandle, value, strlen(value));
606  retval->n = 0;
607  retval->next = h->umacro; // by placing it up front we mask out the old macro until we +nil+ it
608  h->umacro = retval;
609 }

611 // =============================================================================
612 static ABCTRACK *abc_new_track(ABCHANDLE *h, const char *voice, int pos)
613 // =============================================================================
614 {
615  ABCTRACK *retval;
616  if( !pos ) global_voiceno++;
617  retval = (ABCTRACK *)_mm_calloc(h->trackhandle, 1,sizeof(ABCTRACK));
618  retval->next = NULL;
619  retval->vno = global_voiceno;
620  retval->vpos = pos;
621  retval->tiedvpos = pos;
622  retval->instr = 1;
623  strncpy(retval->v, voice, 20);
624  retval->v[20] = '\0';
625  retval->head = NULL;
626  retval->tail = NULL;
627  retval->capostart = NULL;
628  retval->tienote = NULL;
629  retval->mute = 0;
630  retval->chan = 0;
631  retval->transpose = 0;
632  retval->volume = h->track? h->track->volume: 120;
633  retval->slidevoltime = 0;
634  retval->slidevol = 0;
635  retval->legato = 0;
636  return retval;
637 }

649 static int abc_interval(const char *s, const char *d)
650 {
651  const char *p;
652  int i,j,k;
653  int n,oct,m[2];
654  for( j=0; j<2; j++ ) {
655  if( j ) p = d;
656  else p = s;
657  switch(p[0]) {
658  case '^':
659  n = p[1];
660  i = 2;
661  break;
662  case '_':
663  n = p[1];
664  i = 2;
665  break;
666  case '=':
667  n = p[1];
668  i = 2;
669  break;
670  default:
671  n = p[0];
672  i = 1;
673  break;
674  }
675  for( k=0; k<25; k++ )
676  if( n == sig[7][k] )
677  break;
678  oct = 4; // ABC note pitch C is C4 and pitch c is C5
679  if( k > 12 ) {
680  oct++;
681  k -= 12;
682  }
683  while( p[i] == ',' || p[i] == '\'' ) {
684  if( p[i] == ',' )
685  oct--;
686  else
687  oct++;
688  i++;
689  }
690  m[j] = k + 12 * oct;
691  }
692  return m[0] - m[1];
693 }
694 
695 static int abc_transpose(const char *v)
696 {
697  int i,j,t;
698  const char *m = "B", *mv = "";
699  t = 0;
700  global_octave_shift = 99;
701  for( ; *v && *v != ']'; v++ ) {
702  if( !strncasecmp(v,"t=",2) ) {
703  v+=2;
704  if( *v=='-' ) {
705  j = -1;
706  v++;
707  }
708  else j = 1;
709  v+=abc_getnumber(v,&i);
710  t += i * j;
711  global_octave_shift = 0;
712  }
713  if( !strncasecmp(v,"octave=",7) ) {
714  v+=7;
715  if( *v=='-' ) {
716  j = -1;
717  v++;
718  }
719  else j = 1;
720  v+=abc_getnumber(v,&i);
721  t += i * j * 12;
722  global_octave_shift = 0;
723  }
724  if( !strncasecmp(v,"transpose=",10) ) {
725  v+=10;
726  if( *v=='-' ) {
727  j = -1;
728  v++;
729  }
730  else j = 1;
731  v+=abc_getnumber(v,&i);
732  t += i * j;
733  global_octave_shift = 0;
734  }
735  if( !strncasecmp(v,"octave=",7) ) { // used in kv304*.abc
736  v+=7;
737  if( *v=='-' ) {
738  j = -1;
739  v++;
740  }
741  else j = 1;
742  v+=abc_getnumber(v,&i);
743  t += i * j * 12;
744  global_octave_shift = 0;
745  }
746  if( !strncasecmp(v,"m=",2) ) {
747  v += 2;
748  mv = v; // get the pitch for the middle staff line
749  while( *v && *v != ' ' && *v != ']' ) v++;
750  global_octave_shift = 0;
751  }
752  if( !strncasecmp(v,"middle=",7) ) {
753  v += 7;
754  mv = v; // get the pitch for the middle staff line
755  while( *v && *v != ' ' && *v != ']' ) v++;
756  global_octave_shift = 0;
757  }
758  if( !strncasecmp(v,"clef=",5) )
759  v += 5;
760  j = 1;
761  if( !strncasecmp(v,"treble",6) ) {
762  j = 0;
763  v += 6;
764  switch( *v ) {
765  case '1': v++; m = "d"; break;
766  case '2': v++;
767  default: m = "B"; break;
768  case '3': v++; m = "G"; break;
769  case '4': v++; m = "E"; break;
770  case '5': v++; m = "C"; break;
771  }
772  global_octave_shift = 0;
773  }
774  if( j && !strncasecmp(v,"bass",4) ) {
775  m = "D,";
776  j = 0;
777  v += 4;
778  switch( *v ) {
779  case '1': v++; m = "C"; break;
780  case '2': v++; m = "A,"; break;
781  case '3': v++; m = "F,"; break;
782  case '4': v++;
783  default: m = "D,"; break;
784  case '5': v++; m = "B,,"; break;
785  }
786  if( global_octave_shift == 99 )
787  global_octave_shift = -2;
788  }
789  if( j && !strncasecmp(v,"tenor",5) ) {
790  j = 0;
791  v += 5;
792  switch( *v ) {
793  case '1': v++; m = "G"; break;
794  case '2': v++; m = "E"; break;
795  case '3': v++; m = "C"; break;
796  case '4': v++;
797  default: m = "A,"; break;
798  case '5': v++; m = "F,"; break;
799  }
800  if( global_octave_shift == 99 )
801  global_octave_shift = 1;
802  }
803  if( j && !strncasecmp(v,"alto",4) ) {
804  j = 0;
805  v += 4;
806  switch( *v ) {
807  case '1': v++; m = "G"; break;
808  case '2': v++; m = "E"; break;
809  case '3': v++;
810  default: m = "C"; break;
811  case '4': v++; m = "A,"; break;
812  case '5': v++; m = "F,"; break;
813  }
814  if( global_octave_shift == 99 )
815  global_octave_shift = 1;
816  }
817  if( j && strchr("+-",*v) && *v && v[1]=='8' ) {
818  switch(*v) {
819  case '+':
820  t += 12;
821  break;
822  case '-':
823  t -= 12;
824  break;
825  }
826  v += 2;
827  if( !strncasecmp(v,"va",2) ) v += 2;
828  global_octave_shift = 0;
829  j = 0;
830  }
831  if( j ) {
832  while( *v && *v != ' ' && *v != ']' ) v++;
833  }
834  }
835  if( strlen(mv) > 0 ) // someone set the middle note
836  t += abc_interval(mv, m);
837  if( global_octave_shift == 99 )
838  global_octave_shift = 0;
839  return t;
840 }

842 // =============================================================================
843 static ABCTRACK *abc_locate_track(ABCHANDLE *h, const char *voice, int pos)
844 // =============================================================================
845 {
846  ABCTRACK *tr, *prev, *trunused;
847  char vc[21];
848  int i, trans=0, voiceno=0, instrno = 1, channo = 0;
849  for( ; *voice == ' '; voice++ ) ; // skip leading spaces
850  for( i=0; i+1 < sizeof(vc) && *voice && *voice != ']' && *voice != '%' && !isspace(*voice); voice++ ) // can work with inline voice instructions
851  vc[i++] = *voice;
852  vc[i] = '\0';
853  prev = NULL;
854  trunused = NULL;
855  if( !pos ) trans = abc_transpose(voice);
856  for( tr=h->track; tr; tr=tr->next ) {
857  if( tr->vno == 0 ) {
858  if( !trunused ) trunused = tr; // must reuse mastertrack (h->track) as first
859  }
860  else {
861  if( !strncasecmp(tr->v, vc, 20) ) {
862  if( tr->vpos == pos )
863  return tr;
864  trans = tr->transpose;
865  global_octave_shift = tr->octave_shift;
866  voiceno = tr->vno;
867  instrno = tr->instr;
868  channo = tr->chan;
869  }
870  }
871  prev = tr;
872  }
873  if( trunused ) {
874  tr = trunused;
875  if( pos ) {
876  tr->vno = voiceno;
877  tr->instr = instrno;
878  tr->chan = channo;
879  }
880  else {
881  global_voiceno++;
882  tr->vno = global_voiceno;
883  tr->instr = 1;
884  tr->chan = 0;
885  }
886  tr->vpos = pos;
887  tr->tiedvpos = pos;
888  strncpy(tr->v, vc, 20);
889  tr->v[20] = '\0';
890  tr->mute = 0;
891  tr->transpose = trans;
892  tr->octave_shift = global_octave_shift;
893  tr->volume = h->track->volume;
894  tr->tienote = NULL;
895  tr->legato = 0;
896  return tr;
897  }
898  tr = abc_new_track(h, vc, pos);
899  if( pos ) {
900  tr->vno = voiceno;
901  tr->instr = instrno;
902  tr->chan = channo;
903  }
904  tr->transpose = trans;
905  tr->octave_shift = global_octave_shift;
906  if( prev ) prev->next = tr;
907  else h->track = tr;
908  return tr;
909 }

978 // first track is dirigent, remove all control events from other tracks
979 // to keep the information where the events should be relative to note events
980 // in the same tick the ticks are octated and four added for note events
981 // the control events that come before the note events get a decremented tick,
982 // those that come after get an incremented tick, for example:
983 // ctrl ctrl note ctrl ctrl note
984 // original: t t t t t+1 t+1
985 // recoded: 8t+1 8t+2 8t+4 8t+5 8t+11 8t+12
986 static void abc_remove_unnecessary_events(ABCHANDLE *h)
987 {
988  ABCTRACK *tp,*ptp;
989  ABCEVENT *ep, *el;
990  uint32_t ct, et;
991  int d;
992  ptp = NULL;
993  for( tp=h->track; tp; tp=tp->next ) {
994  el = NULL;
995  ep = tp->head;
996  ct = 0;
997  d = -3;
998  while( ep ) {
999  et = ep->tracktick;
1000  ep->tracktick <<= 3;
1001  ep->tracktick += 4;
1002  if( ep->flg == 1 ) {
1003  ep->tracktick += d;
1004  d++;
1005  if( d == 0 ) d = -1;
1006  if( d == 4 ) d = 3;
1007  if( tp!=h->track ) ep->cmd = cmdhide;
1008  switch( ep->cmd ) {
1009  case cmdhide:
1010  case cmdsync:
1011  if( el ) {
1012  el->next = ep->next;
1013  if( !el->next )
1014  tp->tail = el;
1015  _mm_free(h->trackhandle,ep);
1016  ep = el->next;
1017  }
1018  else {
1019  tp->head = ep->next;
1020  if( !tp->head )
1021  tp->tail = NULL;
1022  _mm_free(h->trackhandle,ep);
1023  ep = tp->head;
1024  }
1025  break;
1026  default:
1027  el = ep;
1028  ep = ep->next;
1029  break;
1030  }
1031  }
1032  else {
1033  el = ep;
1034  ep = ep->next;
1035  d = 1;
1036  }
1037  if( et > ct )
1038  d = -3;
1039  ct = et;
1040  }
1041  if( !tp->head ) { // no need to keep empty tracks...
1042  if( ptp ) {
1043  ptp->next = tp->next;
1044  _mm_free(h->trackhandle,tp);
1045  tp = ptp;
1046  }
1047  else if (tp->next) {
1048  h->track = tp->next;
1049  _mm_free(h->trackhandle,tp);
1050  tp = h->track;
1051  } else {
1052  break;
1053  }
1054  }
1055  ptp = tp; // remember previous track
1056  }
1057 }

1059 // set ticks back, and handle partbreaks
1060 static void abc_retick_events(ABCHANDLE *h)
1061 {
1062  ABCTRACK *tp;
1063  ABCEVENT *ep;
1064  uint32_t et, tt=0, at = abcticks(64 * h->speed);
1065  for( tp=h->track; tp; tp=tp->next ) {
1066  // make ticks relative
1067  tt = 0;
1068  for( ep=tp->head; ep; ep=ep->next ) {
1069  et = ep->tracktick >> 3;
1070  ep->tracktick = et - tt;
1071  tt = et;
1072  }
1073  // make ticks absolute again, skipping no-op partbreaks
1074  tt = 0;
1075  for( ep=tp->head; ep; ep=ep->next ) {
1076  ep->tracktick += tt;
1077  tt = ep->tracktick;
1078  if( ep->flg == 1 && ep->cmd == cmdpartbrk ) {
1079  if( tt % at ) {
1080  tt += at;
1081  tt /= at;
1082  tt *= at;
1083  ep->tracktick -= abcticks(h->speed); // break plays current row
1084  }
1085  else ep->cmd = cmdhide;
1086  }
1087  }
1088  }
1089 }

1091 // make sure every track has the control events it needs, this way it is not
1092 // necessary to have redundant +segno+ +D.C.+ etc in the voices, the first voice
1093 // is the master, it is pointed to by the member 'track' in the ABCHANDLE
1094 static void abc_synchronise_tracks(ABCHANDLE *h)
1095 {
1096  ABCTRACK *tp;
1097  uint32_t tm; // tracktime in master
1098  ABCEVENT *em, *es, *et, *ec; // events in master, slave, slave temporary and copied event
1099  if( !h || !h->track ) return;
1100  abc_remove_unnecessary_events(h);
1101  for( tp = h->track->next; tp; tp = tp->next ) {
1102  for( em=h->track->head; em; em=em->next ) {
1103  if( em->flg == 1 ) { // some kind of control event
1104  switch( em->cmd ) {
1105  case cmdchord:
1106  case cmdhide:
1107  case cmdtempo:
1108  case cmdsync:
1109  break;
1110  default: // check to see if copy is necessary
1111  ec = abc_copy_event(h, em);
1112  tm = em->tracktick;
1113  es = tp->head; // allways search from the begin...
1114  for( et=es; et && et->tracktick <= tm; et=et->next )
1115  es = et;
1116  if( es == NULL || es->tracktick > tm ) { // special case: head of track
1117  ec->next = es;
1118  tp->head = ec;
1119  }
1120  else {
1121  ec->next = es->next;
1122  es->next = ec;
1123  }
1124  break;
1125  }
1126  }
1127  }
1128  }
1129  abc_retick_events(h);
1130 }

1182 static int abc_dynamic_volume(ABCTRACK *tp, uint32_t tracktime, int vol)
1183 {
1184  uint32_t slidetime;
1185  int voldelta;
1186  if( tp->mute ) return 0;
1187  if( tp->slidevol == 0 ) return vol;
1188  if( tracktime < tp->slidevoltime ) return vol;
1189  slidetime = modticks(tracktime - tp->slidevoltime);
1190  voldelta = (slidetime * 15) / 64 / 6; // slide from say mf up to f in one pattern's time
1191  if( tp->slidevol > -2 && voldelta > 15 ) voldelta = 15; // never to much dynamics
1192  if( tp->slidevol > 0 ) vol += voldelta;
1193  else vol -= voldelta;
1194  if( vol < 2 ) vol = 2; // xmms divides this by 2....
1195  if( vol > 127 ) vol = 127;
1196  return vol;
1197 }

1232 static ABCTRACK *abc_track_with_note_tied(ABCHANDLE *h, uint32_t tracktime, int n, int oct)
1233 {
1234  int vn, vp;
1235  ABCTRACK *tp;
1236  ABCEVENT *e;
1237  tp = h->tp;
1238  vn = tp->vno;
1239  vp = tp->vpos;
1240  for( tp = h->track; tp; tp = tp->next ) {
1241  if( tp->vno == vn ) {
1242  e = tp->tienote;
1243  if( e && e->tracktick < tracktime
1244  && e->par[octave] == oct && abs(e->par[note] - n) < 3 ) {
1245  if( tp->vpos != vp ) tp->tiedvpos = vp;
1246  h->tp = tp;
1247  return tp;
1248  }
1249  }
1250  }
1251  tp = h->tp;
1252  vp = tp->tiedvpos;
1253  if( tp->vpos != vp ) {
1254  // chord note track allready returned in previous call

1257  tp->tiedvpos = h->tp->vpos;
1258  h->tp = tp;
1259  return tp;
1260  }
1261  }

1266 static int abc_add_noteon(ABCHANDLE *h, int ch, const char *p, uint32_t tracktime, char *barkey, int vol, ABCEVENT_X_EFFECT fx, int fxop)
1267 {
1268  ABCEVENT *e;
1269  ABCTRACK *tp;
1270  int i,j,k;
1271  int n,oct;
1272  char d[6];
1273  tp = h->tp;
1274  switch(ch) {
1275  case '^':
1276  if( p[0] == '^' ) {
1277  n = p[1];
1278  i = 2;
1279  ch = 'x';
1280  }
1281  else {
1282  n = p[0];
1283  i = 1;
1284  }
1285  break;
1286  case '_':
1287  if( p[0] == '_' ) {
1288  n = p[1];
1289  i = 2;
1290  ch = 'b';
1291  }
1292  else {
1293  n = p[0];
1294  i = 1;
1295  }
1296  break;
1297  case '=':
1298  n = p[0];
1299  i = 1;
1300  break;
1301  default:
1302  n = ch;
1303  i = 0;
1304  break;
1305  }
1306  for( k=0; k<51; k++ ) {
1307  if( n == barkey[k] )
1308  break;
1309  }
1310  j = k;
1311  if( k > 24 )
1312  k -= 25; // had something like A# over Bb key F signature....
1313  if( i ) {
1314  // propagate accidentals if necessary
1315  // DON'T do redundant accidentals they're always relative to C-scale
1316  for( k=0; k<25; k++ ) {
1317  if( n == sig[7][k] )
1318  break;
1319  }
1320  if( k < 25 ) { // only do real notes...
1321  switch(ch) {
1322  case 'x':
1323  k++;
1324  case '^':
1325  k++;
1326  break;
1327  case 'b':
1328  k--;
1329  case '_':
1330  k--;
1331  break;
1332  case '=':
1333  break;
1334  }
1335  if( j < 25 ) // was it not A# over Bb?
1336  barkey[j] = ' ';
1337  barkey[k] = n;
1338  }
1339  }
1340  oct = 3; // ABC note pitch C is C4 and pitch c is C5
1341  if( k < 25 ) {
1342  k += tp->transpose;
1343  while( k > 12 ) {
1344  oct++;
1345  k -= 12;
1346  }
1347  while( k < 0 ) {
1348  oct--;
1349  k += 12;
1350  }
1351  d[note] = 23 + k; // C0 is midi notenumber 24
1352  }
1353  else
1354  d[note] = 0; // someone has doen ^X3 or something like it...
1355  while( p[i] && strchr(",'",p[i]) ) {
1356  if( p[i]==',' ) oct--;
1357  else oct++;
1358  i++;
1359  tp->octave_shift = 0; // forget we ever had to look at it
1360  }
1361  if( tp->octave_shift )
1362  tp->transpose += 12 * tp->octave_shift;
1363  oct += tp->octave_shift;
1364  tp->octave_shift = 0; // after the first note we never have to look at it again
1365  if( oct < 0 ) oct = 0;
1366  if( oct > 9 ) oct = 9;
1367  d[octave] = oct;
1368  d[smpno] = pat_gmtosmp(tp->instr);
1369  d[volume] = abc_dynamic_volume(tp, tracktime, vol);
1370  d[effect] = fx; // effect
1371  d[effoper] = fxop;
1372  tp = abc_track_with_note_tied(h, tracktime, d[note], oct);
1373  if( tp->tienote ) {
1374  if( tp->tienote->par[note] != d[note] ) {
1375  if( abs(tp->tienote->par[note] - d[note]) < 3 ) {
1376  // may be tied over bar symbol, recover local accidental to barkey
1377  k = tp->tienote->par[note] - 23 - tp->transpose;
1378  while( k < 0 ) k += 12;
1379  while( k > 12 ) k -= 12;
1380  if( (isupper(n) && barkey[k+12] == ' ') || (islower(n) && barkey[k] == ' ') ) {
1381  barkey[j] = ' ';
1382  if( isupper(n) )
1383  barkey[k] = n;
1384  else
1385  barkey[k+12] = n;
1386  d[note] = tp->tienote->par[note];
1387  d[octave] = tp->tienote->par[octave];
1388  }
1389  }
1390  }
1391  }
1392  if( tp->tienote
1393  && tp->tienote->par[note] == d[note]
1394  && tp->tienote->par[octave] == d[octave] ) {
1395  for( e = tp->tienote; e; e = e->next ) {
1396  if( e->par[note] == 0 && e->par[octave] == 0 ) { // undo noteoff
1397  e->flg = 1;
1398  e->cmd = cmdhide;
1399  e->lpar = 0;
1400  break;
1401  }
1402  }
1403  tp->tienote->tiednote = 1; // mark him for the pattern writers
1404  for( j=i; isdigit(p[j]) || p[j]=='/'; j++ ) ; // look ahead to see if this one is tied too
1405  if( p[j] != '-' ) // is this note tied too?
1406  tp->tienote = NULL; // if not the tie ends here...
1407  return i;
1408  }
1409  tp->tienote = NULL;
1410  if( tp->tail
1411  && tp->tail->tracktick == tracktime
1412  && tp->tail->par[note] == 0
1413  && tp->tail->par[octave] == 0 ) {
1414  for( j=0; j<6; j++ )
1415  tp->tail->par[j] = d[j];
1416  }
1417  else {
1418  e = abc_new_event(h, tracktime, d);
1419  abc_add_event(h, tp, e);
1420  }
1421  if( i > 0 && p[i-1] == '"' ) {
1422  i--; // someone coded a weird note like ^"E"
1423  abc_message("strange note encountered scanning %s", h->line);
1424  }
1425  return i;
1426 }

1637 {

1643  i += abc_getexpr(p+i+1, number);

1724 // evaluate [Q:"string" n1/m1 n2/m2 n3/m3 n4/m4=bpm "string"]
1725 // minimal form [Q:"string"]
1726 // most used form [Q: 1/4=120]
1727 static int abc_extract_tempo(const char *p, int invoice)
1728 {
1729  int nl, nd, ns, in, tempo;
1730  int nl1=0, nd1, notes, state;
1731  const char *q;
1732  in = 0;
1733  nl = 0;
1734  nd = 1;
1735  ns = 120;
1736  notes = 0;
1737  state = 0;
1738  for( q=p; *q; q++ ) {
1739  if( in ) {
1740  if( *q=='"' )
1741  in = 0;
1742  }
1743  else {
1744  if( *q == ']' ) break;
1745  switch( *q ) {
1746  case '"':
1747  in = 1;
1748  break;
1749  case '/':
1750  notes++;
1751  state = 1;
1752  nl1 = ns;
1753  break;
1754  case '=':
1755  break;
1756  default:
1757  if( isdigit(*q) ) {
1758  if( state ) {
1759  q+=abc_getnumber(q,&nd1)-1;
1760  state = 0;
1761  nl = nl * nd1 + nl1 * nd;
1762  nd = nd * nd1;
1763  }
1764  else
1765  q+=abc_getnumber(q,&ns)-1;
1766  }
1767  break;
1768  }
1769  }
1770  }
1771  if( !notes ) {
1772  nl = 1;
1773  nd = 4;
1774  }
1775  if( !nd ) tempo = 120;
1776  else tempo = ns * nl * 4 / nd; // mod tempo is really BPM where one B is equal to a quartnote
1777  if( tempo <= 0 )
1778  tempo = 120;
1779  if( invoice ) {
1780  nl = global_tempo_factor;
1781  nd = global_tempo_divider;
1782  }
1783  global_tempo_factor = 1;
1784  global_tempo_divider = 1;
1785  while( tempo/global_tempo_divider > 255 )
1786  global_tempo_divider++;
1787  tempo /= global_tempo_divider;
1788  while( tempo * global_tempo_factor < 256 )
1789  global_tempo_factor++;
1790  global_tempo_factor--;
1791  tempo *= global_tempo_factor;
1792  if( tempo * 3 < 512 ) {
1793  global_tempo_factor *= 3;
1794  global_tempo_divider *= 2;
1795  tempo = (tempo * 3) / 2;
1796  }
1797  if( invoice ) {
1798  if( nl != global_tempo_factor || nd != global_tempo_divider ) {
1799  ns = (tempo * nl * global_tempo_divider) / (nd * global_tempo_factor);
1800  if( ns > 31 && ns < 256 ) {
1801  tempo = ns;
1802  global_tempo_factor = nl;
1803  global_tempo_divider = nd;
1804  }
1805  else
1806  abc_message("Failure: inconvenient tempo change in middle of voice (%s)", p);
1807  }
1808  }
1809  return tempo;
1810 }

1812 static void abc_set_parts(char **d, char *p)
1813 {
1814  int i,j,k,m,n;
1815  char *q;
1816 #ifdef NEWMIKMOD
1817  static MM_ALLOC *h;
1818  if( *d ) _mmalloc_close(h);
1819 #else
1820  if( *d ) free(*d);
1821 #endif
1822  *d = 0;
1823  if( !p ) return;
1824  for( i=0; p[i] && p[i] != '%'; i++ ) {
1825  if( !strchr("ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ().0123456789 ",p[i]) ) {
1826  abc_message("invalid characters in part string scanning P:%s", p);
1827  return;
1828  }
1829  }
1830 #ifdef NEWMIKMOD
1831  h = _mmalloc_create("Load_ABC_parts", NULL);
1832 #endif
1833  // decode constructs like "((AB)2.(CD)2)3.(AB)E2" to "ABABCDCDABABCDCDABABCDCDABEE"
1834  // first compute needed storage...
1835  j=0;
1836  k=0;
1837  for( i=0; p[i] && p[i] != '%'; i++ ) {
1838  if( isupper(p[i]) ) {
1839  j++;
1840  }
1841  if( isdigit(p[i]) ) {
1842  n=abc_getnumber(p+i,&k);
1843  if( k == 0 )
1844  k = 1;
1845  if( p[i-1] == ')' )
1846  j *= k; // never mind multiple parens, just take the worst case
1847  else
1848  j += k-1;
1849  i += n-1;
1850  }
1851  }
1852  q = (char *)_mm_calloc(h, j+1, sizeof(char)); // enough storage for the worst case
1853  // now copy bytes from p to *d, taking parens and digits in account
1854  j = 0;
1855  for( i=0; p[i] && p[i] != '%'; i++ ) {
1856  if( isdigit(p[i]) || isupper(p[i]) || p[i] == '(' || p[i] == ')' ) {
1857  if( p[i] == ')' ) {
1858  for( n=j; n > 0 && q[n-1] != '('; n-- ) ; // find open paren in q
1859  // q[n+1] to q[j] contains the substring that must be repeated
1860  if( n > 0 ) {
1861  for( k = n; k<j; k++ ) q[k-1] = q[k]; // shift to the left...
1862  j--;
1863  }
1864  else {
1865  abc_message("Warning: Unbalanced right parens in P: definition %s",p);
1866  break;
1867  }
1868  n = j - n + 1; // number of repeatable characters
1869  i += abc_getnumber(p+i+1,&k);
1870  while( k-- > 1 ) {
1871  for( m=0; m<n; m++ ) {
1872  q[j] = q[j-n];
1873  j++;
1874  }
1875  }
1876  continue;
1877  }
1878  if( isdigit(p[i]) ) {
1879  n = abc_getnumber(p+i,&k);
1880  i += n - 1;
1881  while( k-- > 1 ) {
1882  q[j] = q[j-1];
1883  j++;
1884  }
1885  continue;
1886  }
1887  q[j] = p[i];
1888  j++;
1889  }
1890  }
1891  q[j] = '\0';
1892  // remove any left over parens
1893  for( i=0; i<j; i++ ) {
1894  if( q[i] == '(' ) {
1895  abc_message("Warning: Unbalanced left parens in P: definition %s",p);
1896  for( k=i; k<j; k++ ) q[k] = q[k+1];
1897  j--;
1898  }
1899  }
1900  *d = q;
1901 }

1903 static void abc_appendpart(ABCHANDLE *h, ABCTRACK *tp, uint32_t pt1, uint32_t pt2)
1904 {
1905  ABCEVENT *e, *ec;
1906  uint32_t dt;
1907  dt = tp->tail->tracktick - pt1;
1908  for( e=tp->head; e && e->tracktick <= pt2; e=e->next ) {
1909  if( e->tracktick >= pt1 ) {
1910  if( e->flg != 1 || e->cmd == cmdsync || e->cmd == cmdchord ) {
1911  if( e != tp->tail ) {
1912  // copy this event at tail
1913  ec = abc_copy_event(h,e);
1914  ec->tracktick += dt;
1915  ec->part = '*';
1916  tp->tail->next = ec;
1917  tp->tail = ec;
1918  }
1919  }
1920  }
1921  }
1922  abc_add_sync(h, tp, pt2 + dt); // make sure there is progression...
1923 }

1925 static uint32_t abc_pattracktime(ABCHANDLE *h, uint32_t tracktime)
1926 {
1927  ABCEVENT *e;
1928  uint32_t dt,et,pt=abcticks(64 * h->speed);
1929  if(!h || !h->track || !h->track->head ) return 0;
1930  dt = 0;
1931  for( e=h->track->head; e && e->tracktick <= tracktime; e=e->next ) {
1932  if( e->flg == 1 && e->cmd == cmdpartbrk ) {
1933  et = e->tracktick + dt;
1934  if( et % pt ) {
1935  et += pt;
1936  et /= pt;
1937  et *= pt;
1938  dt = et - e->tracktick;
1939  }
1940  }
1941  }
1942  return (tracktime + dt);
1943 }

1950 static void abc_stripoff(ABCHANDLE *h, ABCTRACK *tp, uint32_t tt)
1951 {
1952  ABCEVENT *e1, *e2;
1953  e2 = NULL;
1954  for( e1 = tp->head; e1 && e1->tracktick <= tt; e1=e1->next )
1955  e2 = e1;
1956  if( e2 ) {
1957  e1 = e2->next;
1958  tp->tail = e2;
1959  e2->next = NULL;
1960  }
1961  else {
1962  e1 = tp->tail;
1963  tp->head = NULL;
1964  tp->tail = NULL;
1965  }
1966  while( e1 ) {
1967  e2 = e1->next;
1968  _mm_free(h->trackhandle,e1);
1969  e1 = e2;
1970  }

1973 static void abc_keeptiednotes(ABCHANDLE *h, uint32_t fromtime, uint32_t totime) {
1974  ABCTRACK *tp;
1975  ABCEVENT *e,*n,*f;
1976  if( totime <= fromtime ) return;
1977  for( tp=h->track; tp; tp=tp->next ) {
1978  if( tp->vno ) { // if track is in use...
1979  n = NULL;
1980  for( e=tp->head; e && e->tracktick < fromtime; e = e->next )
1981  if( e->flg != 1 ) n = e; // remember it when it is a note event
1982  if( n && n->tiednote ) { // we've a candidate to tie over the break
1983  while( e && e->tracktick < totime ) e=e->next; // skip to other part
1984  if( e && e->tracktick == totime ) { // if this is on begin row of this part
1985  f = NULL;
1986  while( !f && e && e->tracktick == totime ) {
1987  if( e->flg != 1 ) f = e;
1988  e = e->next;
1989  }
1990  if( f && f->par[note] ) { // pfoeie, we've found a candidate
1991  if( abs(n->par[note] - f->par[note]) < 3 ) { // undo the note on
1992  f->flg = 1;
1993  f->cmd = cmdhide;
1994  f->lpar = 0;
1995  }
1996  }
1997  }
1998  }
1999  }
2000  }
2001 }

2003 static uint32_t abc_fade_tracks(ABCHANDLE *h, char *abcparts, uint32_t ptt[27])
2004 {
2005  ABCTRACK *tp;
2006  ABCEVENT *e0;
2007  char *p;
2008  int vol;
2009  uint32_t pt1, pt2;
2010  uint32_t tt;
2011  tt = h->track->tail->tracktick;
2012  for( tp=h->track->next; tp; tp=tp->next ) {
2013  if( !tp->tail ) abc_add_sync(h, tp, tt); // no empty tracks please...
2014  if( tp->tail->tracktick > tt ) abc_stripoff(h, tp, tt); // should not happen....
2015  if( tp->tail->tracktick < tt ) abc_add_sync(h, tp, tt);
2016  }
2017  for( tp=h->track; tp; tp=tp->next ) {
2018  vol = 127;
2019  e0 = tp->tail;
2020  if( tp->slidevol != -2 ) {
2021  tp->slidevol = -2;
2022  tp->slidevoltime = e0->tracktick;
2023  }
2024  tp->mute = 0; // unmute track for safety, notes in a muted track already have zero volume...
2025  while( vol > 5 ) {
2026  for( p=abcparts; *p && vol > 5; p++ ) {
2027  pt1 = ptt[*p-'A'];
2028  pt2 = ptt[*p-'A'+1];
2029  abc_appendpart(h, tp, pt1, pt2);
2030  vol = abc_dynamic_volume(tp, tp->tail->tracktick, 127);
2031  }
2032  }
2033  abc_fade_track(tp,e0);
2034  }
2035  return h->track->tail->tracktick;
2036 }

2038 static void abc_song_to_parts(ABCHANDLE *h, char **abcparts, BYTE partp[27][2])
2039 {
2040  uint32_t starttick;
2041  ABCEVENT *e;
2042  int i, fading, loop, normal, partno, partsegno, partloop, partcoda, parttocoda, partfine, skip, x, y;
2043  int vmask[27],nextp[27];
2044  uint32_t ptt[27];
2045  char buf[256]; // must be enough, mod's cannot handle more than 240 patterns
2046  char *pfade;
2047  if( !h || !h->track || !h->track->capostart ) return;
2048  strcpy(buf,"A"); // initialize our temporary array
2049  i = 1;
2050  loop = 1;
2051  partno = 0;
2052  partsegno = 0;
2053  partloop = 0;
2054  partcoda = -1;
2055  parttocoda = -1;
2056  partfine = -1;
2057  starttick = h->track->capostart->tracktick;
2058  ptt[0] = starttick;
2059  vmask[0] = -1;
2060  nextp[0] = 1;
2061  for( e=h->track->capostart; e; e=e->next ) {
2062  if( e->flg == 1 ) {
2063  switch( e->cmd ) {
2064  case cmdpartbrk:
2065  if( e->tracktick > starttick) {
2066  starttick = e->tracktick; // do not make empty parts
2067  if( partno < 26 ) {
2068  partno++;
2069  ptt[partno] = starttick;
2070  }
2071  if( i < 255 ) buf[i++] = partno+'A';
2072  vmask[partno] = -1;
2073  nextp[partno] = partno+1;
2074  }
2075  break;
2076  case cmdloop:
2077  partloop = partno;
2078  loop = 1; // start counting anew...
2079  break;
2080  case cmdvariant:
2081  vmask[partno] = e->lpar;
2082  break;
2083  case cmdjump:
2084  x = 0;
2085  fading = 0;
2086  normal = 0;
2087  skip = 0;
2088  pfade = &buf[i];
2089  switch( e->par[jumptype] ) {
2090  case jumpfade:
2091  fading = 1;
2092  case jumpnormal:
2093  normal = 1;
2094  x = partloop;
2095  loop++;
2096  break;
2097  case jumpdsfade:
2098  fading = 1;
2099  case jumpdasegno:
2100  x = partsegno;
2101  break;
2102  case jumpdcfade:
2103  fading = 1;
2104  case jumpdacapo:
2105  x = 0;
2106  break;
2107  default:
2108  x = 0;
2109  break;
2110  }
2111  if( vmask[partno] != -1 ) nextp[partno] = x;
2112  if( partno < 26 ) ptt[partno+1] = e->tracktick; // for handling ties over breaks
2113  while( x <= partno ) {
2114  if( skip == 1 && x == partcoda ) skip = 0;
2115  y = !skip;
2116  if( y ) {
2117  if( !normal ) {
2118  if( x == partfine ) skip = 2;
2119  if( x == parttocoda ) skip = 1;
2120  y = !skip;
2121  }
2122  if( !(vmask[x] & (1<<loop)) ) y = 0;
2123  }
2124  if( y ) {
2125  if( i < 255 ) buf[i++] = x+'A';
2126  if( nextp[x] != x + 1 ) loop++;
2127  x = nextp[x];
2128  }
2129  else
2130  x++;
2131  }
2132  if( fading && partno < 25 && i < 254 ) { // add single part with fading tracks
2133  partno++;
2134  ptt[partno] = e->tracktick;
2135  buf[i] = '\0'; // close up pfade with zero byte
2136  starttick = abc_fade_tracks(h, pfade, ptt);
2137  buf[i++] = partno+'A';
2138  partno++;
2139  ptt[partno] = starttick;
2140  buf[i++] = partno+'A'; // one extra to throw away...
2141  e = h->track->tail; // this is the edge of the world captain...
2142  }
2143  break;
2144  case cmdtocoda:
2145  parttocoda = partno;
2146  break;
2147  case cmdcoda:
2148  partcoda = partno;
2149  break;
2150  case cmdfine:
2151  partfine = partno;
2152  break;
2153  case cmdsegno:
2154  partsegno = partno;
2155  break;
2156  }
2157  }
2158  e->part = partno+'a'; // small caps for generated parts...
2159  }
2160  i--; // strip off last partno
2161  if( partno > 0 ) partno--;
2162  buf[i] = '\0';
2163  if( i > 1 ) {
2164  for( i=1; buf[i]; i++ ) {
2165  if( buf[i] != buf[i-1] + 1 ) {
2166  x = buf[i-1] - 'A';
2167  y = buf[i] - 'A';
2168  abc_keeptiednotes(h, ptt[x+1], ptt[y]);
2169  }
2170  }
2171  }
2172  starttick = h->track->tail->tracktick;
2173  ptt[partno+1] = starttick;
2174  for( i=0; i<=partno; i++ ) {
2175  partp[i][0] = abc_patno(h, ptt[i]);
2176  partp[i][1] = abc_patno(h, ptt[i+1]);
2177  }
2178  // calculate end point of last part
2179  starttick = abc_pattracktime(h, starttick);
2180  if( starttick % abcticks(64 * h->speed) )
2181  partp[partno][1]++;
2182  abc_set_parts(abcparts, buf);
2183 }

2216 static void abc_substitute(ABCHANDLE *h, char *target, char *s)
2217 {
2218  char *p, *q;
2219  int i;
2220  int l = strlen(target);
2221  int n = strlen(s);
2222  if (l <= 0 ||n <= 0 || strstr(s, target))
2223  return;
2224  while( (p=strstr(h->line, target)) ) {
2225  if( (i=strlen(h->line)) + n - l >= (int)h->len ) {
2226  h->line = (char *)_mm_recalloc(h->allochandle, h->line, h->len<<1, sizeof(char));
2227  h->len <<= 1;
2228  p=strstr(h->line, target);
2229  }
2230  if( n > l ) {
2231  for( q=&h->line[i]; q>p; q-- ) q[n-l] = q[0];
2232  for( q=s; *q; q++ ) *p++ = *q;
2233  }
2234  else {

2236  strcat(p,p+l);
2237  }
2238  }

2241 static void abc_preprocess(ABCHANDLE *h, ABCMACRO *m)
2242 {
2243  int i, j, k, l, a, b;
2244  if( m->n ) {
2245  k = m->n - m->name;
2246  for( i=0; i<14; i++ ) {
2247  char t[strlen(m->name) + 1];
2248  strcpy(t, m->name);
2249  t[k] = "CDEFGABcdefgab"[i];
2250  l = strlen(m->subst);
2251  char s[2 * l + 1];
2252  char *p = s;
2253  for( j=0; j<l; j++ ) {
2254  a = m->subst[j];
2255  if( a > 'g' && islower(a) ) {
2256  b = a - 'n';
2257  a = "CDEFGABCDEFGABcdefgabcdefgab"[i+b+7];
2258  *p++ = a;
2259  if( i+b < 0 )
2260  *p++ = ',';
2261  else if( i+b > 13 )
2262  *p++ = '\'';
2263  }
2264  else *p++ = a;
2265  }
2266  *p = '\0';
2267  abc_substitute(h, t, s);
2268  }
2269  }
2270  else
2271  abc_substitute(h, m->name, m->subst);
2272 }

2275 {

2277  ABCMACRO *mp;

2298 static int abc_parse_decorations(ABCHANDLE *h, ABCTRACK *tp, const char *p)
2299 {
2300  int vol=0;
2301  if( !strncmp(p,"mp",2) ) vol = 75;
2302  if( !strncmp(p,"mf",2) ) vol = 90;
2303  if( !strncmp(p,"sfz",3) ) vol = 100;
2304  if( *p == 'p' ) {
2305  vol = 60;
2306  while( *p++ == 'p' ) vol -= 15;
2307  if( vol < 1 ) vol = 1;
2308  }
2309  if( *p == 'f' ) {
2310  vol = 105;
2311  while( *p++ == 'f' ) vol += 15;
2312  if( vol > 135 ) vol = 127; // ffff
2313  if( vol > 127 ) vol = 125; // fff
2314  }
2315  if( vol ) {
2316  tp->volume = vol;
2317  if( tp == h->track ) { // copy volume over to all voice tracks
2318  for( ; tp; tp=tp->next ) {
2319  if( tp->vpos == 0 || tp->vpos > DRONEPOS2 ) tp->volume = vol;
2320  }
2321  tp = h->track;
2322  }
2323  }
2324  return tp->volume;
2325 }

2534 // =============================================================================
2535 #ifdef NEWMIKMOD
2536 static void ABC_ReadPatterns(UNIMOD *of, ABCHANDLE *h, int numpat)
2537 // =============================================================================
2538 {
2539  int pat,row,i,ch,trillbits;
2540  BYTE n,ins,vol;
2541  ABCTRACK *t;
2542  ABCEVENT *e, *en, *ef, *el;
2543  uint32_t tt1, tt2;
2544  UNITRK_EFFECT eff;
2545 
2546  // initialize start points of event list in tracks
2547  for( t = h->track; t; t = t->next ) t->capostart = t->head;
2548  trillbits = 0; // trill effect admininstration: one bit per channel, max 32 channnels
2549  for( pat = 0; pat < numpat; pat++ ) {
2550  utrk_reset(of->ut);
2551  for( row = 0; row < 64; row++ ) {
2552  tt1 = abcticks((pat * 64 + row ) * h->speed);
2553  tt2 = tt1 + abcticks(h->speed);
2554  ch = 0;
2555  for( e=abc_next_global(h->track->capostart); e && e->tracktick < tt2; e=abc_next_global(e->next) ) {
2556  if( e && e->tracktick >= tt1 ) { // we have a tempo event in this row
2557  switch( e->cmd ) {
2558  case cmdtempo:
2559  eff.effect = UNI_GLOB_TEMPO;
2560  eff.param.u = e->lpar;
2561  eff.framedly = UFD_RUNONCE;
2562  utrk_write_global(of->ut, &eff, PTMEM_TEMPO);
2563  break;
2564  case cmdpartbrk:
2565  eff.effect = UNI_GLOB_PATBREAK;
2566  eff.param.u = 0;
2567  eff.framedly = UFD_RUNONCE;
2568  utrk_write_global(of->ut, &eff, UNIMEM_NONE);
2569  break;
2570  }
2571  }
2572  }
2573  for( t = h->track; t; t = t->next ) {
2574  for( e=abc_next_note(t->capostart); e && e->tracktick < tt1; e=abc_next_note(e->next) )
2575  t->capostart = e;
2576  i = 0;
2577  ef = NULL;
2578  en = e;
2579  el = e;
2580  for( ; e && e->tracktick < tt2; e=abc_next_note(e->next) ) { // we have a note event in this row
2581  t->capostart = e;
2582  i++;
2583  if( e->par[volume] ) {
2584  if( !ef ) ef = e;
2585  el = e;
2586  }
2587  }
2588  if( i ) {
2589  trillbits &= ~(1<<ch);
2590  utrk_settrack(of->ut, ch);
2591  if( i == 1 || ef == el || !ef ) { // only one event in this row
2592  if( ef ) e = ef;
2593  else e = en;
2594  el = t->capostart;
2595  i = e->par[note] + ((e->par[octave])*12);
2596  if( t->chan == 10 ) {
2597  n = pat_gm_drumnote(i) + 23;
2598  ins = pat_gmtosmp(pat_gm_drumnr(i));
2599  }
2600  else {
2601  n = pat_modnote(i);
2602  ins = e->par[smpno];
2603  }
2604  eff.framedly = modticks(e->tracktick - tt1);
2605  vol = e->par[volume];
2606  if( e->par[effect] == accent ) {
2607  vol += vol / 10;
2608  if( vol > 127 ) vol = 127;
2609  }
2610  if (vol <= 0) {}
2611  else if( el->par[volume] == 0 ) {
2612  eff.framedly = modticks(el->tracktick - tt1);
2613  eff.param.u = 0;
2614  eff.param.byte_a = n;
2615  eff.param.byte_b = ins;
2616  eff.effect = UNI_NOTEKILL;
2617  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, UNIMEM_NONE);
2618  }
2619  else {
2620  switch( e->par[effect] ) {
2621  case trill:
2622  eff.effect = UNI_VIBRATO_DEPTH;
2623  eff.param.u = 12; // depth 1.5
2624  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, PTMEM_VIBRATO_DEPTH);
2625  eff.effect = UNI_VIBRATO_SPEED;
2626  eff.param.u = 48; // speed 12
2627  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, PTMEM_VIBRATO_SPEED);
2628  trillbits |= (1<<ch);
2629  break;
2630  case bow:
2631  eff.effect = UNI_PITCHSLIDE;
2632  eff.framedly = (h->speed/2)|UFD_RUNONCE;
2633  eff.param.s = 2;
2634  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, (e->par[effoper])? PTMEM_PITCHSLIDEUP: PTMEM_PITCHSLIDEDN);
2635  break;
2636  default:
2637  break;
2638  }
2639  if( eff.framedly ) {
2640  eff.param.u = 0;
2641  eff.param.byte_a = n;
2642  eff.param.byte_b = ins;
2643  eff.effect = UNI_NOTEDELAY;
2644  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, UNIMEM_NONE);
2645  }
2646  }
2647  utrk_write_inst(of->ut, ins);
2648  utrk_write_note(of->ut, n); // <- normal note
2649  pt_write_effect(of->ut, 0xc, vol);
2650  }
2651  else {
2652  // two notes in one row, use FINEPITCHSLIDE runonce effect
2653  // start first note on first tick and framedly runonce on seconds note tick
2654  // use volume and instrument of last note
2655  if( t->chan == 10 ) {
2656  i = el->par[note] + ((el->par[octave])*12);
2657  n = pat_gm_drumnote(i) + 23;
2658  ins = pat_gmtosmp(pat_gm_drumnr(i));
2659  i = n; // cannot change instrument here..
2660  }
2661  else {
2662  i = ef->par[note] + ((ef->par[octave])*12);
2663  n = pat_modnote(i);
2664  ins = el->par[smpno];
2665  i = pat_modnote(el->par[note] + ((el->par[octave])*12));
2666  }
2667  vol = el->par[volume];
2668  eff.effect = UNI_PITCHSLIDE;
2669  eff.framedly = modticks(el->tracktick - tt1)|UFD_RUNONCE;
2670  eff.param.s = ((i > n)?i-n:n-i);
2671  utrk_write_inst(of->ut, ins);
2672  utrk_write_note(of->ut, n); // <- normal note
2673  pt_write_effect(of->ut, 0xc, vol);
2674  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, (i > n)? PTMEM_PITCHSLIDEUP: PTMEM_PITCHSLIDEDN);
2675  }
2676  }
2677  else { // no new notes, keep on trilling...
2678  if( trillbits & (1<<ch) ) {
2679  utrk_settrack(of->ut, ch);
2680  eff.effect = UNI_VIBRATO_DEPTH;
2681  eff.param.u = 12; // depth 1.5
2682  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, PTMEM_VIBRATO_DEPTH);
2683  eff.effect = UNI_VIBRATO_SPEED;
2684  eff.param.u = 60; // speed 15
2685  utrk_write_local(of->ut, &eff, PTMEM_VIBRATO_SPEED);
2686  }
2687  }
2688  ch++;
2689  }
2690  utrk_newline(of->ut);
2691  }
2692  if(!utrk_dup_pattern(of->ut,of)) return;
2693  }
2694 }

2698 static int ABC_ReadPatterns(MODCOMMAND *pattern[], WORD psize[], ABCHANDLE *h, int numpat, int channels)
2699 // =====================================================================================
2700 {
2701  int pat,row,i,ch,trillbits;
2702  BYTE n,ins,vol;
2703  ABCTRACK *t;
2704  ABCEVENT *e, *en, *ef, *el;
2705  uint32_t tt1, tt2;
2706  MODCOMMAND *m;
2707  int patbrk, tempo;
2708  if( numpat > MAX_PATTERNS ) numpat = MAX_PATTERNS;
2709 
2710  // initialize start points of event list in tracks
2711  for( t = h->track; t; t = t->next ) t->capostart = t->head;
2712  trillbits = 0; // trill effect admininstration: one bit per channel, max 32 channnels
2713  for( pat = 0; pat < numpat; pat++ ) {
2714  pattern[pat] = CSoundFile::AllocatePattern(64, channels);
2715  if( !pattern[pat] ) return 0;
2716  psize[pat] = 64;
2717  for( row = 0; row < 64; row++ ) {
2718  tt1 = abcticks((pat * 64 + row ) * h->speed);
2719  tt2 = tt1 + abcticks(h->speed);
2720  ch = 0;
2721  tempo = 0;
2722  patbrk = 0;
2723  for( e=abc_next_global(h->track->capostart); e && e->tracktick < tt2; e=abc_next_global(e->next) ) {
2724  if( e && e->tracktick >= tt1 ) { // we have a tempo event in this row
2725  switch( e->cmd ) {
2726  case cmdtempo:
2727  tempo = e->lpar;
2728  break;
2729  case cmdpartbrk:
2730  patbrk = 1;
2731  break;
2732  }
2733  }
2734  }
2735  for( t = h->track; t; t = t->next ) {
2736  for( e=abc_next_note(t->capostart); e && e->tracktick < tt1; e=abc_next_note(e->next) ) ;
2737  i = 0;
2738  ef = NULL;
2739  en = e;
2740  el = e;
2741  for( ; e && e->tracktick < tt2; e=abc_next_note(e->next) ) { // we have a note event in this row
2742  t->capostart = e;
2743  i++;
2744  if( e->par[volume] ) {
2745  if( !ef ) ef = e;
2746  el = e;
2747  }
2748  }
2749  m = &pattern[pat][row * channels + ch];
2750  m->param = 0;
2751  m->command = CMD_NONE;
2752  if( i ) {
2753  trillbits &= ~(1<<ch);
2754  if( i == 1 || ef == el || !ef ) { // only one event in this row
2755  if( ef ) e = ef;
2756  else e = en;
2757  el = t->capostart;
2758  i = e->par[note] + ((e->par[octave])*12);
2759  if( t->chan == 10 ) {
2760  n = pat_gm_drumnote(i) + 23;
2761  ins = pat_gmtosmp(pat_gm_drumnr(i));
2762  }
2763  else {
2764  n = pat_modnote(i);
2765  ins = e->par[smpno];
2766  }
2767  vol = e->par[volume]/2;
2768  if( e->par[volume] > 0 ) {
2769  if( e->par[effect] == accent ) vol += vol / 20;
2770  if( vol > 64 ) vol = 64;
2771  if( el->par[volume] == 0 ) { // note cut
2772  m->param = el->tracktick - tt1;
2773  m->command = CMD_S3MCMDEX;
2774  m->param |= 0xC0;
2775  }
2776  else {
2777  switch( e->par[effect] ) {
2778  case trill:
2779  m->command = CMD_VIBRATO;
2780  m->param = 0xC2; // speed 12 depth 2
2781  trillbits |= (1<<ch);
2782  break;
2783  case bow:
2784  m->command = CMD_XFINEPORTAUPDOWN;
2785  m->param |= (e->par[effoper])? 0x12: 0x22;
2786  break;
2787  default:
2788  m->param = modticks(e->tracktick - tt1);
2789  if( m->param ) { // note delay
2790  m->command = CMD_S3MCMDEX;
2791  m->param |= 0xD0;
2792  }
2793  break;
2794  }
2795  }
2796  }
2797  m->instr = ins;
2798  m->note = n; // <- normal note
2799  m->volcmd = VOLCMD_VOLUME;
2800  m->vol = vol;
2801  }
2802  else {
2803  // two notes in one row, use FINEPITCHSLIDE runonce effect
2804  // start first note on first tick and framedly runonce on seconds note tick
2805  // use volume and instrument of last note
2806  if( t->chan == 10 ) {
2807  i = el->par[note] + ((el->par[octave])*12);
2808  n = pat_gm_drumnote(i) + 23;
2809  ins = pat_gmtosmp(pat_gm_drumnr(i));
2810  i = n; // cannot change instrument here..
2811  }
2812  else {
2813  i = ef->par[note] + ((ef->par[octave])*12);
2814  n = pat_modnote(i);
2815  ins = el->par[smpno];
2816  i = pat_modnote(el->par[note] + ((el->par[octave])*12));
2817  }
2818  vol = el->par[volume]/2;
2819  if( vol > 64 ) vol = 64;
2820  m->instr = ins;
2821  m->note = n; // <- normal note
2822  m->volcmd = VOLCMD_VOLUME;
2823  m->vol = vol;
2824  m->param = ((i > n)?i-n:n-i);
2825  if( m->param < 16 ) {
2826  if( m->param ) {
2827  m->command = CMD_XFINEPORTAUPDOWN;
2828  m->param |= (i > n)? 0x10: 0x20;
2829  }
2830  else { // retrigger same note...
2831  m->command = CMD_RETRIG;
2832  m->param = modticks(el->tracktick - tt1);
2833  }
2834  }
2835  else
2836  m->command = (i > n)? CMD_PORTAMENTOUP: CMD_PORTAMENTODOWN;
2837  }
2838  }
2839  else { // no new notes, keep on trilling...
2840  if( trillbits & (1<<ch) ) {
2841  m = &pattern[pat][row * channels + ch];
2842  m->command = CMD_VIBRATO;
2843  m->param = 0; // inherited from first effect
2844  m->instr = 0;
2845  m->note = 0;
2846  m->volcmd = 0;
2847  m->vol = 0;
2848  }
2849  }
2850  if( m->param == 0 && m->command == CMD_NONE ) {
2851  if( tempo ) {
2852  m->command = CMD_TEMPO;
2853  m->param = tempo;
2854  tempo = 0;
2855  }
2856  else {
2857  if( patbrk ) {
2858  m->command = CMD_PATTERNBREAK;
2859  patbrk = 0;
2860  }
2861  }
2862  }
2863  ch++;
2864  }
2865  if( tempo || patbrk ) return 1;
2866  }
2867  }
2868  return 0;
2869 }

2873 static int ABC_Key(const char *p)
2874 {
2875  int i,j;
2876  char c[8] = {0};
2877  const char *q;
2878  while( isspace(*p) ) p++;
2879  i = 0;
2880  q = p;
2881  for( i=0; i<8 && *p && *p != ']'; p++ ) {
2882  if( isspace(*p) ) {
2883  while( isspace(*p) ) p++;
2884  if( strncasecmp(p, "min", 3) && strncasecmp(p, "maj", 3) )
2885  break;
2886  }
2887  c[i] = *p;
2888  i++;
2889  }
2890  c[i] = '\0';
2891  if( !strcmp(c,"Hp") || !strcmp(c,"HP") ) // highland pipes
2892  strcpy(c,"Bm"); // two sharps at c and f
2893  if( !strcasecmp(c+1, "minor") ) i=2;
2894  if( !strcasecmp(c+2, "minor") ) i=3;
2895  if( !strcasecmp(c+1, "major") ) i=1;
2896  if( !strcasecmp(c+2, "major") ) i=2;
2897  if( !strcasecmp(c+1, "min") ) i=2;
2898  if( !strcasecmp(c+2, "min") ) i=3;
2899  if( !strcasecmp(c+1, "maj") ) i=1;
2900  if( !strcasecmp(c+2, "maj") ) i=2;
2901  for( ; i<6; i++ )
2902  c[i] = ' ';
2903  c[i] = '\0';
2904  for( i=0; keySigs[i]; i++ ) {
2905  for( j=10; j<46; j+=6 )
2906  if( !strncasecmp(keySigs[i]+j, c, 6) )
2907  return i;
2908  }
2909  abc_message("Failure: Unrecognised K: field %s", q);
2910  return 7;
2911 }

2916  while( *p && !isspace(*p) && *p != ']') p++;
2917  while( isspace(*p) ) p++;
2918  return p;

2931 static void abc_addchordname(const char *s, int len, const int *notes)
2932 // adds chord name and note set to list of known chords
2933 {
2934  int i, j;
2935  if(strlen(s) > 7) {
2936  abc_message("Failure: Chord name cannot exceed 7 characters, %s", s);
2937  return;
2938  }
2939  if(len > 6) {
2940  abc_message("Failure: Named chord cannot have more than 6 notes, %s", s);
2941  return;
2942  }
2943  for( i=0; i < chordsnamed; i++ ) {
2944  if(strcmp(s, chordname[i]) == 0) {
2945  /* change chord */
2946  chordlen[i] = len;
2947  for(j = 0; j < len; j++) chordnotes[i][j] = notes[j];
2948  return;
2949  }
2950  }
2951  if(chordsnamed > MAXCHORDNAMES - 1)
2952  abc_message("Failure: Too many Guitar Chord Names used, %s", s);
2953  else {
2954  strcpy(chordname[chordsnamed], s);
2955  chordlen[chordsnamed] = len;
2956  for(j = 0; j < len; j++) chordnotes[chordsnamed][j] = notes[j];
2957  chordsnamed++;
2958  }
2959 }

3339 static void abc_add_drum(ABCHANDLE *h, uint32_t tracktime, uint32_t bartime)
3340 {
3341  ABCEVENT *e;

3344  int i, g, steps, gnote, gsteps, nnum;
3345  steps = abc_drum_steps(h->drum);
3346  ctime = h->barticks;
3347  // look up the last event in tpr drumtrack
3348  tp = abc_locate_track(h, h->tpr->v, DRUMPOS);

3353  else rtime = (etime - bartime) % h->barticks;

3355  rtime *= steps;
3356  rtime += stime;
3357  gsteps = strlen(h->drum)/2;

3370  nnum = pat_gm_drumnote(h->drumins[g]);

3372  abc_add_noteoff(h,tp,etime + ( rtime + ctime * i )/steps);
3373  }
3374  if( ++g == gsteps ) g = 0;
3375  rtime += ctime * i;
3376  }

3483 // %%MIDI beat a b c n
3484 //
3485 // controls the way note velocities are selected. The first note in a bar has
3486 // velocity a. Other "strong" notes have velocity b and all the rest have velocity
3487 // c. a, b and c must be in the range 0-128. The parameter n determines which
3488 // notes are "strong". If the time signature is x/y, then each note is given
3489 // a position number k = 0, 1, 2 .. x-1 within each bar. Note that the units for
3490 // n are not the unit note length. If k is a multiple of n, then the note is
3491 // "strong". The volume specifiers !ppp! to !fff! are equivalent to the
3492 // following :
3493 //
3494 // !ppp! = %%MIDI beat 30 20 10 1
3495 // !pp! = %%MIDI beat 45 35 20 1
3496 // !p! = %%MIDI beat 60 50 35 1
3497 // !mp! = %%MIDI beat 75 65 50 1
3498 // !mf! = %%MIDI beat 90 80 65 1
3499 // !f! = %%MIDI beat 105 95 80 1
3500 // !ff! = %%MIDI beat 120 110 95 1
3501 // !fff! = %%MIDI beat 127 125 110 1
3502 static void abc_MIDI_beat(ABCHANDLE *h, const char *p)
3503 {
3504  int i,j;
3505  h->beat[0] = 127;
3506  h->beat[1] = 125;
3507  h->beat[2] = 110;
3508  h->beat[3] = 1;
3509  for( j=0; j<4; j++ ) {
3510  while( isspace(*p) ) p++;
3511  if( *p ) {
3512  p += abc_getnumber(p, &i);
3513  if( i < 0 ) i = 0;
3514  if( i > 127 ) i = 127;
3515  h->beat[j] = i;
3516  }
3517  }
3518  if( h->beat[3] == 0 ) h->beat[3] = 1; // BB Ruud says: do not let you make mad
3519 }
3520 
3521 //
3522 // %%MIDI beatstring <string of f, m and p>
3523 //
3524 // This provides an alternative way of specifying where the strong and weak
3525 // stresses fall within a bar. 'f' means velocity a (normally strong), 'm'
3526 // means velocity b (medium velocity) and 'p' means velocity c (soft velocity).
3527 // For example, if the time signature is 7/8 with stresses on the first, fourth
3528 // and sixth notes in the bar, we could use the following
3529 //
3530 // %%MIDI beatstring fppmpmp
3531 static void abc_MIDI_beatstring(ABCHANDLE *h, const char *p)
3532 {
3533  while( isspace(*p) ) p++;
3534  if( h->beatstring ) _mm_free(h->allochandle, h->beatstring);
3535  if( strlen(p) )
3536  h->beatstring = DupStr(h->allochandle,p,strlen(p)+1);
3537  else
3538  h->beatstring = NULL;
3539 }
3540 
3541 static int abc_beat_vol(ABCHANDLE *h, int abcvol, int barpos)
3542 {
3543  int vol;
3544  if( h->beatstring ) {
3545  vol = (h->beat[2] * 9) / 10;
3546  if( barpos < (int)strlen(h->beatstring) ) {
3547  switch(h->beatstring[barpos]) {
3548  case 'f':
3549  vol = h->beat[0];
3550  break;
3551  case 'm':
3552  vol = h->beat[1];
3553  break;
3554  case 'p':
3555  vol = h->beat[2];
3556  break;
3557  default:
3558  break;
3559  }
3560  }
3561  }
3562  else {
3563  if( (barpos % h->beat[3]) == 0 ) {
3564  if( barpos )
3565  vol = h->beat[1];
3566  else
3567  vol = h->beat[0];
3568  }
3569  else
3570  vol = h->beat[2];
3571  }
3572  vol *= abcvol;
3573  vol /= 128;
3574  return vol;
3575 }

3586 static int abc_partpat_to_orderlist(BYTE partp[27][2], const char *abcparts, ABCHANDLE *h, BYTE **list, int orderlen)
3587 {
3588  int t, partsused;
3589  const char *p;
3590  BYTE *orderlist = *list;
3591  static int ordersize = 0;
3592  if( *list == NULL ) {
3593  ordersize = 128;
3594  orderlist = (BYTE *)_mm_calloc(h->ho, ordersize, sizeof(BYTE));
3595  *list = orderlist;
3596  }
3597  if( abcparts ) {
3598  partsused = 0;
3599  for( p = abcparts; *p; p++ ) {
3600  for( t = partp[*p - 'A'][0]; t < partp[*p - 'A'][1]; t++ ) {
3601  if( orderlen == ordersize ) {
3602  ordersize <<= 1;
3603  orderlist = (BYTE *)_mm_recalloc(h->ho, orderlist, ordersize, sizeof(BYTE));
3604  *list = orderlist;
3605  }
3606  orderlist[orderlen] = t;
3607  orderlen++;
3608  partsused++;
3609  }
3610  }
3611  if( partsused ) return orderlen;
3612  }
3613  // some fool wrote a P: string in the header but didn't use P: in the body
3614  for( t = partp[26][0]; t < partp[26][1]; t++ ) {
3615  if( orderlen == ordersize ) {
3616  ordersize <<= 1;
3617  orderlist = (BYTE *)_mm_recalloc(h->ho, orderlist, ordersize, sizeof(BYTE));
3618  *list = orderlist;
3619  }
3620  orderlist[orderlen] = t;
3621  orderlen++;
3622  }
3623  return orderlen;
3624 }

3626 static void abc_globalslide(ABCHANDLE *h, uint32_t tracktime, int slide)
3627 {
3628  ABCTRACK *tp;

3634  tp->slidevoltime = tracktime;
3635  if( slide == 2 )
3636  tp->slidevol = 0;
3637  }
3638  if( tp->slidevol > -2 && slide < 2 )
3639  tp->slidevol = slide;
3640  }
3641  if( h->track && h->track->tail
3642  && hslide != slide && slide == -2
3643  && h->track->tail->tracktick >= tracktime ) {
3644  // need to update jumptypes in mastertrack from tracktime on...

3649  case jumpfade:
3650  e->par[jumptype] = jumpfade;

3655  break;
3656  case jumpdasegno:
3657  case jumpdsfade:
3658  e->par[jumptype] = jumpdsfade;
3659  break;
3660  }
3661  }
3662  }
3663  }

3674 static void abc_MIDI_command(ABCHANDLE *h, char *p, char delim) {
3675  int t;
3676  // interpret some of the possibilitys
3677  if( !strncmp(p,"bassprog",8) && isspace(p[8]) ) h->abcbassprog = abc_MIDI_getprog(p+8)+1;
3678  if( !strncmp(p,"bassvol",7) && isspace(p[7]) ) h->abcbassvol = abc_MIDI_getnumber(p+7);
3679  if( !strncmp(p,"beat",4) && isspace(p[4]) ) abc_MIDI_beat(h, p+4);
3680  if( !strncmp(p,"beatstring",10) && isspace(p[10]) ) abc_MIDI_beatstring(h, p+4);
3681  if( !strncmp(p,"chordname",9) && isspace(p[9]) ) abc_MIDI_chordname(p+9);
3682  if( !strncmp(p,"chordprog",9) && isspace(p[9]) ) h->abcchordprog = abc_MIDI_getprog(p+9)+1;
3683  if( !strncmp(p,"chordvol",8) && isspace(p[8]) ) h->abcchordvol = abc_MIDI_getnumber(p+8);
3684  if( !strncmp(p,"drone",5) && isspace(p[5]) ) abc_MIDI_drone(p+5, &h->dronegm, h->dronepitch, h->dronevol);
3685  if( !strncmp(p,"droneoff",8) && (p[8]=='\0' || p[8]==delim || isspace(p[8])) ) h->droneon = 0;
3686  if( !strncmp(p,"droneon",7) && (p[7]=='\0' || p[7]==delim || isspace(p[7])) ) h->droneon = 1;
3687  t = h->drumon;
3688  if( !strncmp(p,"drum",4) && isspace(p[4]) ) {
3689  h->drumon = abc_MIDI_drum(p+4, h);
3690  if( h->drumon ) --h->drumon;
3691  else h->drumon = t;
3692  }
3693  if( !strncmp(p,"drumoff",7) && (p[7]=='\0' || p[7]==delim || isspace(p[7])) ) h->drumon = 0;
3694  if( !strncmp(p,"drumon",6) && (p[6]=='\0' || p[6]==delim || isspace(p[6])) ) h->drumon = 1;
3695  if( t != h->drumon ) {
3696  if( h->drumon && !h->tpr ) h->tpr = h->track;
3697  if( h->tpr ) abc_add_drum_sync(h, h->tpr, h->tracktime); // don't start drumming from the beginning of time!
3698  if( h->tpr && !h->drumon ) h->tpr = NULL;
3699  }
3700  t = h->gchordon;
3701  if( !strncmp(p,"gchord",6) && (p[6]=='\0' || p[6]==delim || isspace(p[6])) ) {
3702  h->gchordon = abc_MIDI_gchord(p+6, h);
3703  if( h->gchordon ) --h->gchordon;
3704  else h->gchordon = t;
3705  }
3706  if( !strncmp(p,"gchordoff",9) && (p[9]=='\0' || p[9]==delim || isspace(p[9])) ) h->gchordon = 0;
3707  if( !strncmp(p,"gchordon",8) && (p[8]=='\0' || p[8]==delim || isspace(p[8])) ) h->gchordon = 1;
3708  if( t != h->gchordon ) {
3709  if( h->tpc ) abc_add_gchord_syncs(h, h->tpc, h->tracktime);
3710  }
3711  if( !strncmp(p,"channel",7) && isspace(p[7]) )
3712  abc_MIDI_channel(p+8, h->tp = abc_check_track(h, h->tp), h);
3713  if( !strncmp(p,"program",7) && isspace(p[7]) )
3714  abc_MIDI_program(p+8, h->tp = abc_check_track(h, h->tp), h);
3715  if( !strncmp(p,"voice",5) && isspace(p[5]) )
3716  abc_MIDI_voice(p+6, h->tp = abc_check_track(h, h->tp), h);
3717  if( !strncmp(p,"legato",6) && (p[6]=='\0' || p[6]==delim || isspace(p[6])) )
3718  abc_MIDI_legato(p+6, h->tp = abc_check_track(h, h->tp));
3719 }

3721 // continuate line that ends with a backslash, can't do this in abc_gets because voice lines
3722 // can have comment lines in between that must be parsed properly, for example:
3723 // [V:1] cdef gabc' |\ << continuation backslash
3724 // %%MIDI program 25
3725 // c'bag fedc |
3726 // informational lines can have this too, so it is rather convoluted code...
3727 static char *abc_continuated(ABCHANDLE *h, MMFILE *mmf, char *p) {
3728  char *pm, *p1, *p2 = 0;
3729  int continued;
3730  pm = p;
3731  while( pm[strlen(pm)-1]=='\\' ) {
3732  p1 = strdup(pm);
3733  if( p2 ) free(p2);
3734  continued = 1;
3735  while( continued ) {
3736  continued = 0;
3737  pm = abc_gets(h, mmf);
3738  if( !pm ) {
3739  abc_message("line not properly continued\n%s", p1);
3740  return p1;
3741  }
3742  while( *pm && isspace(*pm) ) ++pm;
3743  if( !strncmp(pm,"%%",2) ) {
3744  for( p2 = pm+2; *p2 && isspace(*p2); p2++ ) ;
3745  if( !strncmp(p2,"MIDI",4) && (p2[4]=='=' || isspace(p2[4])) ) {
3746  for( p2+=5; *p2 && isspace(*p2); p2++ ) ;
3747  if( *p2 == '=' )
3748  for( p2+=1; *p2 && isspace(*p2); p2++ ) ;
3749  abc_MIDI_command(h,p2,'%');
3750  }
3751  continued = 1;
3752  }
3753  }
3754  p2 = (char *)malloc(strlen(p1)+strlen(pm));
3755  if( !p2 ) {
3756  abc_message("macro line too long\n%s", p1);
3757  return p1;
3758  }
3759  p1[strlen(p1)-1] = '\0'; // strip off the backslash
3760  strcpy(p2,p1);
3761  strcat(p2,pm);
3762  pm = p2;
3763  free(p1);
3764  }
3765  return pm;
3766 }
